		<item>
			<title>The Demon, The Lost, and More</title>
			<link>http://www.helveticablanc.com/updates-2025.html#20250808</link>
			<description>
				<![CDATA[
				<p>July had quite a few releases, starting with more prints from the <a href="https://helveticablanc.bigcartel.com/product/the-wormsong-oracle-deck" target="_blank">Wormsong Oracle Deck</a>:</p>
				<p>
					<a href="20250630-the-demon.html">
						<img src="img/digital/20250630-the-demon.png" alt="A many-armed, abstract, stone-like entity terrorizes a Seeker. In the background, a star is bound with sigils." loading="lazy"><br/>The Demon
					</a>
				</p>
				<p>
					<a href="20250707-the-lost.html">
						<img src="img/digital/20250707-the-lost.png" alt="Three star-like entities fall through the sky, trailing ribbon-like arms. In the background is the silhouette of a large star bound with sigils." loading="lazy"><br/>The Lost
					</a>
				</p>
				<p>
					<a href="20250714-the-angel.html">
						<img src="img/digital/20250714-the-angel.png" alt="Three angels descend upon a seeker with arms outstretched. The first looks like an abstracted clown face with four wings. The second looks like a thorny ring surrounded in eyes, and the third looks like a three-winged star." loading="lazy"><br/>The Angel
					</a>
				</p>
				<p>
					<a href="20250721-the-exile.html">
						<img src="img/digital/20250721-the-exile.png" alt="A massive, star-like entity bound with sigils floats high above the Realms — a world depicted as concentric spheres surrounded by wings." loading="lazy"><br/>The Exile
					</a>
				</p>
				<p>Beyond that, I released two new zines — HOLY! 28 and Marginalia 3! All patrons get digital versions of my zines, and Collector's tier patrons have been receiving physical copies of Marginalia. There's <a href="https://www.patreon.com/helveticablanc" target="_blank">a handful spots left on Patreon</a> if you want to get in on the series!</p>
				<p>
					<a href="https://helveticablanc.itch.io/holy-28" target="_blank">
						<img src="img/zines/holy-28.png" alt="Cover of HOLY! 28"  loading="lazy"><br/>HOLY! 28
					</a>
				</p>
				<p>
					<a href="https://helveticablanc.itch.io/marginalia-3" target="_blank">
						<img src="img/zines/marginalia-3.png" alt="Cover of Marginalia 3"  loading="lazy"><br/>Marginalia 3
					</a>
				</p>
				]]>
			</description>
			<guid>http://www.helveticablanc.com/updates-2025.html#20250808</guid>
			<pubDate>Fri, 08 Aug 2025 23:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
		</item>

		<item>
			<title>The Guide, The Serpent, and More</title>
			<link>http://www.helveticablanc.com/updates-2025.html#20250711</link>
			<description>
				<![CDATA[
				<p>June was a surprisingly productive month, where I released a few more prints from the <a href="https://helveticablanc.bigcartel.com/product/the-wormsong-oracle-deck" target="_blank">Wormsong Oracle Deck</a>:</p>
				<p>
					<a href="20250602-the-guide.html">
						<img src="img/digital/20250602-the-guide.png" alt="A jester-like Hierophant stands within an archway and slowly reaches for a cross-like sigil." loading="lazy"><br/>The Guide
					</a>
				</p>
				<p>
					<a href="20250609-the-serpent.html">
						<img src="img/digital/20250609-the-serpent.png" alt="A winged serpent winds through the composition, surrounding a meditating seeker." loading="lazy"><br/>The Serpent
					</a>
				</p>
				<p>
					<a href="20250616-the-librarian.html">
						<img src="img/digital/20250616-the-librarian.png" alt="A ribbon-like Kīrolisk guides a Seeker through the library. While conversing, the Librarian carrys a book and an offering bowl with a star above it." loading="lazy"><br/>The Librarian
					</a>
				</p>
				<p>
					<a href="20250623-the-offering.html">
						<img src="img/digital/20250623-the-offering.png" alt="A ghost-like Saint and a Seeker gather around an offering bowl. Incense smoke rises from the bowl in waves and fills the composition." loading="lazy"><br/>The Offering
					</a>
				</p>
				<p>I also released a new print for Make a Terrible Comic Day — <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/pseudonymjones.bsky.social/post/3lsd7iiyavk2k" target="_blank">participation was mandatory!</a></p>
				<p>
					<a href="20250624-tides.html">
						<img src="img/digital/20250624-tides.png" alt="Three panels show a person waking up crying, rolling over to reach for an empty space, and then facing upward and letting their tears stain the pillow in a halo around their head. The tears fill the bottom half of the composition like an ocean overtaking the character. The panels are accompanied by the text 'Do you think the sea waits for tides to change too?'. There is a decorative border with a sword, heart, and a liquid falling towards a cup held upward." loading="lazy"><br/>Tides
					</a>
				</p>
				<p>Last but not least, I released the first two issues of Marginalia — my new zine series — in digital format! Collector's tier patrons have been receiving physical copies, and there's <a href="https://www.patreon.com/helveticablanc" target="_blank">still a few spots on Patreon</a> if you want to get in on the new series!</p>
				<p>
					<a href="https://helveticablanc.itch.io/marginalia-1" target="_blank">
						<img src="img/zines/marginalia-1.png" alt="Cover of Marginalia 1"  loading="lazy"><br/>Marginalia 1
					</a>
				</p>
				<p>
					<a href="https://helveticablanc.itch.io/marginalia-2" target="_blank">
						<img src="img/zines/marginalia-2.png" alt="Cover of Marginalia 2"  loading="lazy"><br/>Marginalia 2
					</a>
				</p>
				]]>
			</description>
			<guid>http://www.helveticablanc.com/updates-2025.html#20250711</guid>
			<pubDate>Fri, 11 Jul 2025 23:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
		</item>

		<item>
			<title>The Shepherd, The Reliquary, and More</title>
			<link>http://www.helveticablanc.com/updates-2025.html#20250613</link>
			<description>
				<![CDATA[
				<p>May was a chaotic month, but I managed to release some more prints from the <a href="https://helveticablanc.bigcartel.com/product/the-wormsong-oracle-deck" target="_blank">Wormsong Oracle Deck</a>:</p>
				<p>
					<a href="20250428-the-shepherd.html">
						<img src="img/digital/20250428-the-shepherd.png" alt="A shepherd tends to their cow, who is drawn in a style reminiscent of cave art and has a halo above their horns." loading="lazy"><br/>The Shepherd
					</a>
				</p>
				<p>
					<a href="20250505-the-reliquary.html">
						<img src="img/digital/20250505-the-reliquary.png" alt="A star-like Vessel hovers just above a half-buried column. In the background is a star bound with sigils." loading="lazy"><br/>The Reliquary
					</a>
				</p>
				<p>
					<a href="20250512-the-auroch.html">
						<img src="img/digital/20250512-the-auroch.png" alt="A massive, emaciated, human-faced bull is attended upon and worshipped by ghost-like saints." loading="lazy"><br/>The Auroch
					</a>
				</p>
				<p>
					<a href="20250519-the-guardian.html">
						<img src="img/digital/20250519-the-guardian.png" alt="Skulls and debris line the stairs leading toward an archway. A sphinx stretches, blocking passage through the threshold as she looks down upon a traveler." loading="lazy"><br/>The Guardian
					</a>
				</p>
				<p>
					<a href="20250526-the-threshold.html">
						<img src="img/digital/20250526-the-threshold.png" alt="A living archway greets a Seeker while making a gesture meaning 'as above, so below'. The Seeker bows, reaching for a skull within the threshold." loading="lazy"><br/>The Threshold
					</a>
				</p>
				<p>In other news, my friends over at <a href="https://knaveofcups.com/" target="_blank">Knave of Cups</a> have begun stocking the <a href="https://knaveofcups.com/product/the-wormsong-oracle/" target="_blank">Wormsong Oracle Deck</a>, and they are shipping everywhere except for the EU! The stock ran out within a day, but new stock is on the way and it should be back in the store soon!</p>
				<p>
					<a href="https://knaveofcups.com/product/the-wormsong-oracle/" target="_blank">
						<img src="img/updates/knave-of-cups-wormsong-oracle.jpg" alt="A lovely promotional shot from Knave of Cups. You can see the box and back of the cards with foil stamping, and three cards are laid out in a spread in the front — The Shepherd, the Teacher of Wings, and the Five of Eyes." loading="lazy">
					</a>
				</p>
				]]>
			</description>
			<guid>http://www.helveticablanc.com/updates-2025.html#20250613</guid>
			<pubDate>Fri, 13 Jun 2025 23:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
		</item>

		<item>
			<title>HOLY! 27, The Invocation, and More</title>
			<link>http://www.helveticablanc.com/updates-2025.html#20250509</link>
			<description>
				<![CDATA[
				<p>April marked a return to full capacity, and it kept me quite busy! I started with a new issue of my quarterly zine, HOLY!</p>
				<p>
					<a href="https://helveticablanc.itch.io/holy-27" target="_blank">
						<img src="img/zines/holy-27.png" alt="Cover of HOLY! 27"  loading="lazy"><br/>HOLY! 27
					</a>
				</p>
				<p>I also released several more prints with imagery from the <a href="https://helveticablanc.bigcartel.com/product/the-wormsong-oracle-deck" target="_blank">Wormsong Oracle Deck</a>:</p>
				<p>
					<a href="20250331-the-invocation.html">
						<img src="img/digital/20250331-the-invocation.png" alt="A jester-like Hierophant and their entourage of Saints call down a Herald — an abstract entity with a face like a broken mirror, crowned with a moon and star, and followed by smaller shard-like being with wings." loading="lazy"><br/>The Invocation
					</a>
				</p>
				<p>
					<a href="20250407-the-saints.html">
						<img src="img/digital/20250407-the-saints.png" alt="Several ghost-like Saints gather within ruins and lift an offering bowl with skeletal arms towards a massive, heptagonal void in the sky — the Throne." loading="lazy"><br/>The Saints
					</a>
				</p>
				<p>
					<a href="20250414-the-unknown.html">
